message.content: Before breaking his arm, Cam typed 9 words per minute. After breaking his arm, he typed 6 words per minute. To find the difference in typing speed, we need to subtract the slower speed from the faster one: 9 - 6 = 3 words per minute. Then, we need to multiply this difference by the time: (5 minutes * 3 = 15 fewer words. So, Cam could type 5 fewer words after breaking his arm.<|im_end>
